div.div: Commented on #142 Brotli: "Uncaught Corrupted reserve bit"

This is not necessarily expected behaviour. Content-Encoding documents what encoding the original payload has been altered with. If you put a .br file on your server the original payload technically is the brotli-compressed file itself and Content-Encoding should not be set (unless a further compression was applied on the fly). Sorry, yes, this is correct, I meant it was expected behaviour for my dev server since it passes .br down as if it was on-the-fly encoded. My apologies. But yes, it just seems to be a quirk with the dev server itself rather than JSO. I've actually just learnt this isn't meant to be how the server responds with data, although I suppose it's not the worst thing in the world. Is there any performance improvement of .br directly vs on-the-fly with JSO?
